To move the selection by one character when selecting text in a TextField widget in Flutter, you can define a custom `TextSelectionControls` class and override its `handleHorizontalArrows()` method. Here's an example:

```dart
TextField(
  text: 'Some text to select',
  selectionControls: CustomTextSelectionControls(),
);

class CustomTextSelectionControls extends MaterialTextSelectionControls {
  @override
  handleHorizontalArrows(TextSelectionDelegate delegate, KeyEvent event) {
    final newOffset = delegate.textEditingValue.selection.baseOffset + (event.logicalKey == LogicalKeyboardKey.arrowLeft ? -1 : 1);
    delegate.textEditingValue = delegate.textEditingValue.copyWith(selection: TextSelection.collapsed(offset: newOffset));
