在Flutter的UnitTest中模拟时间，可以使用dartz库中的Clock类来实现。Clock是一个抽象类，提供了获取当前时间、延迟操作、定时操作等方法，可以通过实现Clock来实现对时间的控制。

以下示例演示如何使用Clock类，在测试中模拟时间：

```dart
import 'package:dartz/dartz.dart';

class TestClock implements Clock {
  DateTime _currentTime;

  TestClock(DateTime initialTime) {
    _currentTime = initialTime;
  }

  @override
  DateTime now() => _currentTime;

  void advance(Duration duration) {
    _currentTime = _currentTime.add(duration);
  }
}

void main() {
  test('Test time', () {
    final clock = TestClock(DateTime.utc(2022, 1, 1));
    expect(clock.now(), equals(DateTime.utc(2022, 1, 1)));

    clock.advance(Duration(days: 1));
    expect(clock.now(), equals(DateTime.utc(2022, 1, 2)));
  });
}
```

在此示例中，我们首先实现了一个TestClock类，该类实现了Clock接口，并在构造函数中初始化了当前时间。然后我们在测试中创建了一个TestClock实例，可以通过now()方法获取当前时间，并通过advance()方法模拟时间的前进。最后，我们使用expect()方法来验证时间是否正确。

在Flutter中模拟异步操作是很常见的需求。通常可以使用`FakeAsync`类来控制异步操作的时间。

以下示例演示如何在测试中模拟一个2秒的异步操作：

```dart
import 'package:flutter_test/flutter_test.dart';
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

void main() {
  testWidgets('Test toast', (WidgetTester tester) async {
    // Build a test widget that triggers a toast message.
    final widget = MaterialApp(
      home: Scaffold(
        body: ElevatedButton(
          onPressed: () {
            ScaffoldMessenger.of(tester.element(find.byType(ElevatedButton))).showSnackBar(SnackBar(content: Text('Test toast')));
          },
          child: Text('Show Toast'),
        ),
      ),
    );

    // Pump the widget and trigger the toast.
    await tester.pumpWidget(widget);
    await tester.tap(find.byType(ElevatedButton));
    await tester.pumpAndSettle();

    // Wrap the test in a `FakeAsync` block to control time.
    await tester.runAsync(() async {
      // Wait for 2 seconds.
      await Future.delayed(Duration(seconds: 2));

      // The toast should be gone now.
      expect(find.text('Test toast'), findsNothing);
    });
  });
}
```

在示例中，我们首先创建了一个带有一个ElevatedButton控件的测试widget。该按钮会在点击后通过ScaffoldMessenger来展示一个Snackbar，用于模拟Toast的弹出。

然后，我们使用测试器调度器来启动widget并模拟Toast的弹出。使用pumpAndSettle()方法等待widget完成一切动画和过渡效果。

最后，我们将测试函数包装在`FakeAsync`块中。在`FakeAsync`块中，我们可以使用delayed()方法模拟小部分时间的过去，而不会真正地等待时间。这允许我们快速测试在一段时间之后的状态，而不需要等待实际的等待时间。

最终，我们可以使用expect()方法来检查toast消息是否已经消失。注意，在FakeAsync块之外，我们不需要使用pumpAndSettle()方法来等待Toast消失, 因为我们可以直接在我们自己的时间表上快进2秒钟。

Creating a webview app for Android involves several steps. Follow the instructions below to create a webview app from scratch.

Step 1: Create a new Android Studio project
1. Open Android Studio and click on 'Start a new Android Studio project.'
2. Select 'Empty Activity' and click 'Next.'
3. Enter the application name and package name.
4. Select the 'Language' as 'Java' and choose the 'Minimum API level' as per your requirement. For example, API 19: Android 4.4 (KitKat).
5. Click on 'Finish.'

Step 2: Add internet permission in the AndroidManifest.xml file
Open the AndroidManifest.xml file and add the following line inside the `<manifest>` element:

```xml
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />
```

Step 3: Add a WebView in the activity_main.xml layout file
Open the activity_main.xml file and insert the following code inside the `<RelativeLayout>`:

```xml
<WebView
    android:id="@+id/web_view"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent" />
```

Step 4: Add the required code in the MainActivity.java file

Replace the existing "MainActivity" with the following code:

```java
import androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity;
import android.os.Bundle;
import android.webkit.WebSettings;
import android.webkit.WebView;
import android.webkit.WebViewClient;

public class MainActivity extends AppCompatActivity {
    private WebView webView;

    @Override
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);
        webView = (WebView) findViewById(R.id.web_view);

        WebSettings webSettings = webView.getSettings();
        webSettings.setJavaScriptEnabled(true);

        webView.setWebViewClient(new WebViewClient());

        webView.loadUrl("https://www.example.com");
    }

    @Override
    public void onBackPressed() {
        if (webView.canGoBack()) {
            webView.goBack();
        } else {
            super.onBackPressed();
        }
    }
}
```
Replace 'https://www.example.com' with your desired website URL.

Step 5: Running the app
1. Connect your Android device to your computer or use an emulator.
2. Select the target device from the device drop-down menu in the Android Studio toolbar.
3. Click on the 'Run' button (or press Shift + F10) to run the app.

Your webview app should now display the website URL specified in the MainActivity.java file.

Optional (Step 6): Handling SSL Error

Incase your website uses HTTPS and you want to handle SSL error, add following code snippet in MainActivity.java.

```java
import android.webkit.SslErrorHandler;
import android.net.http.SslError;
```

Add this inside the "onCreate" method.

```java
webView.setWebViewClient(new WebViewClient() {
    @Override
    public void onReceivedSslError(WebView view, SslErrorHandler handler, SslError error) {
        handler.proceed(); // Ignore SSL certificate errors
    }
});
```

This code will ignore SSL certificate errors, but using this method is not suggested for production apps due to security reasons. To properly handle SSL certificate errors, refer to the Android Developers documentation on 'WebSettings'.

